 597:src/setup.c   **** 
 598:src/setup.c   ****   /* CRITICAL: Actively drive ALL motor PWM pins LOW (GPIO output, not AF).
 599:src/setup.c   ****    *
 600:src/setup.c   ****    * With OSSR=0, OSSI=0, MOE=0, the STM32 releases AF control of the pins.
 601:src/setup.c   ****    * The hoverboard PCB has pull-ups on gate driver inputs (HIN/LIN). When
 602:src/setup.c   ****    * pins float HIGH: both high and low-side FETs are ON → phases shorted.
 603:src/setup.c   ****    * A floating HIGH drove the V-phase high-side FET → burned MOSFET.
 604:src/setup.c   ****    *
 605:src/setup.c   ****    * Fix: reconfigure all 12 PWM pins as GPIO output LOW. This actively
 606:src/setup.c   ****    * holds HIN=0 (high-side OFF) and LIN=0 (low-side OFF) → all FETs off
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccgCjHFe.s 			page 32


 607:src/setup.c   ****    * → motor phases truly floating → wheel turns freely.
 608:src/setup.c   ****    *
 609:src/setup.c   ****    * When BLDC ISR enables (enable=1), HAL_TIM_PWM_Start/PWMN_Start will
 610:src/setup.c   ****    * reconfigure the pins back to AF-PP for active motor control.
 611:src/setup.c   ****    *
 612:src/setup.c   ****    * GPIO output PP 50MHz in STM32F1 CRL/CRH: CNF=00, MODE=11 → 0x3
 613:src/setup.c   ****    * Use BSRR upper half (bit-reset = drive LOW): BSRR = (1<<(16+pin))
 614:src/setup.c   ****    */
